Sentencas: The application of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta(LSCF) as a potential cathode working on a BaCe0.54Zr0.36Y0.1O2.95 (BCZY) electrolyte for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell was investigated.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: LSCF nanoceramic powders were synthesized by an activated carbon-assisted sot gel process using metal nitrate-based chemicals.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The LSCF powder was transformed to a slurry and spin-coated onto both surfaces of BCZY pellet to form a symmetrical cell with the configuration of LSCF/BCZY/LSCF.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The symmetrical cell was subsequently sintered at 950 degrees C for 2 h to allow a good contact formation between electrode/electrolyte layers.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The phase structural verification of the calcined powders was investigated by X-Ray diffractometer (XRD).
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Field-emission scanning electron microscopy (FESEM) was employed to examine the morphology of the sintered cell.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The electrochemical behaviour of the symmetrical cell was studied by an electrochemical impedance spectroscopy The formation of a single perovskite LSCF phase with a crystallite size of 20 nm was obtained at 700 degrees C as corroborated by XRD analysis.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The FESEM images showed a good contact between LSCF cathode and BCZY electrolyte at electrode/ electrolyte interfacial layer.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The ASR obtained for LSCF symmetrical cell measured at 700 degrees C with and without Pt current collector is 0.87 and 31.25 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Evaluation of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a Potential Cathode for Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
